review_blob: Bought at ABC beers in The Hague (NL). Subtle Smokey aroma and taste. A bit too acid for my taste. OK.
Dark color with hardly any carbonation. Strong aroma of cacao, coffee and salmiak. Deel, layered taste: sweet, coffee, candies, licorice, caramel. Very smooth as well. Wow!
Hoppy and fresh citrus aroma. Full malty and bitter taste. Some notes of caramel. Nice carbonation! Very good IPA style beer.
Delicious Porter! Welcoming coffee / salmiak / Chocolate aroma. Creamy taste...could be more expressieve.
The smell is promising, but the taste is not rich. Refreshing beer though! Overall a good lager.

On draft at Pintelier in Groningen (NL). Golden coloured beer with big head. Aroma is hoppy, yeasty and floral. Taste is spicy, yeasty, complex mix of hops, deed and balanced bitterness. Very, very delicious!
The color is troubled. Apple, pear, melon, grass and yeast in aroma. The beer tastes hoppy, fresh, yeasty and spicy. Good IPA.
Bottle from brewery de molen. Dark golden beer with small head. Smell is wonderful: flowers, honey, melon, and citrus fruit. Taste is similar, with mild bitterness. Overall, a pleasant IPA!
Dark red / amber colored beer. Smells sweet, rich and complex. I taste caramel, figgs, resins and ripe red fruit. The best barley wine I have tasted so far.
Bottle from ABC beers in the Hague (NL). Dark brown beer. Smells like BBQ! The smokey taste is well balanced. Very good Rauch beer!
Bottle. Cloudy, golden yellow color. Very vivid brew: carbornation and a nice head! Smell is yeasty, the taste is yeasty, refreshing, malty...mmm delicious!
Bottle. Beer smells amazing: citrus, tropical fruits (mango?) and hop. Taste is fruity and bitter. Delicious!

On draught at brewery De Molen in Bodegraven (NL). Dark / red colored. An overwhelming aroma of rum, raisins and red fruit. The taste is similar: very sweet and heavy! Reminds me of port / sherry. Wow! Perhaps, a bit too overwhelming if not paired with cheese or desserts.

On draught at brewery De Molen in Bodengraven. A beautiful beer to see: golden yellow color. I miss some citrus fruit in th smell. The taste is subtle for an IPA: the hops are well balanced! Nice summer beer.
Bottle from sypermarket in Letterfrack, Ireland. Very nice citrus smell. Taste is rather superficial and disappoints me. Ok beer.
Letterfrack, Ireland. Beautiful dark red ale. Smells like honey and vanilla. Soft, sweet caramel taste with a gentle hop finish. Good beer!
33cl bottle at Troch brewery. A dark red beer, without head. Smell is sweet, cherry, vanilla, candy. The taste is well balanced between sour and sweet. Very refreshing!

375 ml bottle bought 6 months ago at the monastery. Smells like smokey whisky, caramal, raisin, rum and some hop. There is little carbonation. The beer tastes a bit smokey, caramel, liquorice, figs and rum. I can clearly taste the finish on whisky barrels. Although a strong beer, I dont notice the alcohol. Good, but not excellent.
beer_name: La Trappe Quadrupel Oak Aged Batch #7

review_blob: Not a special beer. The taste is sweet with hints of honey, toast and malts. It is easy to drink, but there is almost no after taste. I am not going to drink it again.

Bought in Breda (NL). Amusing label on bottle. Aroma and taste are much better than the colour of this beer promises. Taste of coriander, lemon and a bit sweeter than normal Belgian white beers. Overall, very good beer!
